    "ArticleTitle": "Continuing education and community pharmacists in Galicia: a study of opinions.",
    "Pagination": {
      "StartPage": "173",
      "EndPage": "177",
      "MedlinePgn": "173-7"
    },
    "Abstract": {
      "AbstractText": [
        "To determine the opinions of a volunteer group of community pharmacists concerning general and specific issues related to continuing education.",
        "Participants were required to complete questionnaires before and after attendance at a refresher course, and score the relevant options provided on a scale from 0 to 10. The responses of the survey were analyzed to identify preferences and to detect any possible changes in opinion.",
        "Arithmetic means of pharmacists' opinions.",
        "The teaching methods preferred by the community pharmacists were workshops for resolution of practical cases (9 +/- 0.25 and 8.88 +/- 0.13) and the distance-learning computer programmes (6.74 +/- 0.25 and 8.18 +/- 0.20). In selecting which topics that should be taught, the participants gave the highest ratings to healthcare needs (8.75 +/- 0.14 and 8.57 +/- 0.15) and the demands of the pharmacists (8.15 +/- 0.16 and 8.40 +/- 0.16), with pharmaceutical care being the most requested topic (29 points). Participants preferred courses lasting 20 to 50 hours (6.94 +/- 0.26 and 7.89 +/- 0.16), without preference for schedule.",
        "Community pharmacists in Galicia show a great interest in the provision and organization of continuing education activities that meet their needs and expectations."
      ]
    },
